How to generate LLVM code 
/-----------------------------------------------------------------------------\
|                                                                             |
| How to Compile :                                                            |
|                    make clean                                               |
|                    make toplevel.native                                     |
|                                                                             |
| How to execute test script :                                                |
|                    make test                                                |
|                                                                             |
| Available Flags : 
|             [-a] print the AST 
|             [-s] print the SAST 
|             [-l] print the generated LLVM IR 
|             [-c] print the generated LLVM IR and check LLVM is valid
|
| How to run on specific files :                                              |
|                    ./toplevel.native [flag] [filename]                      |
|                                                                             |
\-----------------------------------------------------------------------------/


Programs in testing suite 

/-----------------------------------------------------------------------------\
|
|  1. helloworld.moop     : Prints hello world 
|  2. locals.moop         : Hello world with locals declared in main method
|  3. printint.moop       : Prints an int
|  4. additionreturn.moop : Prints two numbers added 
| 
\



